Bird Seed Candy aka PB & J Power Bites 

Friends, my bird seed bowl recipe has made its way into hundreds of homes + it makes me so happy to share simple + nutritious recipes that are as easy to make as enjoyable to eat!

Now, let’s take all the goodness of the birdseed bowl and turn it into “candy”! 
It’s un-freaking-believable 
Loaded with raspberries, blueberries, chia seeds, hemp hearts + peanut butter… this frozen treat will quickly become a household staple 

Bird Seed Candy 

12oz raspberries
3/4 cup frozen Wymans blueberries 🫐 
1/4 cup chia seeds
1/4 cup hemp hearts
3/4 cup peanut butter (any nut butter)
15oz dark chocolate chips 
2 Tbsp coconut oil
Sea Salt 

In a large bowl, smash the raspberries 
Stir in the blueberries, chia seeds + hemp hearts 

In a seperate bowl, melt the chocolate chips + coconut oil in the microwave 

Grab a mini-muffin silicone mold and get ready to make these irresistible bites! 

Pour 1 tsp of melted chocolate in each mold, spreading to coat the sides 
Pop the mold into the freezer to set (5 min) 
Once chocolate has hardened, add a little peanut butter to the bottom of each cup
On top, add 1/2 Tbsp of the raspberry/seed mixture 
Top with more melted chocolate to cover + sprinkle with sea salt
Pop back into the freezer to set + ENJOY!

Store in freezer in the mold, OR put bird seed bites into a ziploc bag 

inspired by: @plantbased.green

My Pizza Bites are by far one of the most popular party appetizers, hands down. 
The pizza dough is SO fluffy, stuffed with @micelidairy shredded mozzarella and pepperoni - baked to a bubbly perfection. 
You can make these with a multitude of fillings, use your imagination inspired by your favorite pizza toppings! 

The only measuring needed is for the dough ❤️

🥣Pizza Dough🥣
3 1/2 cup warm water
2 packets of Red Star Quick - Rise Yeast 
4 tsp sugar 
8 cup unbleached all-purpose flour 
2 tsp salt
drizzle of olive oil 

Let’s make the dough!
In a small bowl, add the warm water, yeast and sugar.  Gently stir and then allow to sit for 5-8 minutes to bloom. 
In a large bowl, pour in the flour + salt - whisk to combine 
Once the yeast has bloomed, pour it into the flour and mix together until a sticky dough forms 
Add a sprinkle of flour more as needed as you start to knead the dough (simply in the bowl) to form a ball.  Drizzle with a little olive oil 
Cover the bowl with a kitchen towel, and allow the dough to rise for 2 hours 

Once the dough has double in size, punch it down in the middle + get ready to make the pizza bites! 

You’ll need:
Premade pizza dough
@micelidairy shredded mozzarella 
Pepperoni slices 

Pre heat oven to 400°
Use a 14” cake pan or 9x13 baking sheet; grease pan of choice with butter 
Take golf-ball size pieces of pizza dough and flatten slightly into a circle
Add a good pinch of @micelidairy mozzarella cheese + 2 slices of pepperoni 
Fold the edges over fillings, roll into a ball + place onto the cake pan 
Finish filling + rolling, until your pan is full 
Brush pizza bites with a mixture of melted butter, Micelis parmesan cheese, oregano + garlic powder (1/2 stick butter, 1/4 cup parmesan, 1/2 tsp garlic + oregano)

BAKE @ 400° for 30-40 minutes until pizza bites are golden and cooked through 

Enjoy with a side of warm marinara to dip!

My Pizza Bites are a decade old recipe of mine that still to this day are a much-requested appetizer for parties!

Candied Nuts 

These candied nuts have been at family gatherings for as long as I can remember, and just make the holidays extra special. 
Pecans and walnuts are my personal favorite to make! I usually double the recipe for each batch and store seperately. 

1 lb nuts of choice 
1 egg white
1 Tbsp water
1/2 tsp vanilla 
1 cup sugar (you can always use 1/2 cup) 
1 heaping tsp cinnamon 
1/2 tsp salt 
*sea salt for finishing* 

1. whisk together the egg white, water + vanilla until frothy 
2. pour nuts in, toss to coat
3. mix together the sugar, cinnamon + salt and then pour it over the nuts and toss to coat completely
4. bake on a parchment lined baking sheet at 250° for one hour, tossing every 15 minutes 
5. Take out of oven and sprinkle with sea salt. Let cool completely before adding to a jar

Enjoy!

🪩New Years Appetizer🪩
Baked Rueben Egg Rolls 

Everything you love about a rueben sandwich, rolled into an egg roll wrapper, baked – NOT fried! This perfect appetizer can be made days in advance, frozen and warmed through the day of the big party! 
As many of you know, I am a huge sauerkraut lover, so the combo of salty corned beef, tangy sauerkraut, and melted Swiss all rolled together is literally a dream - extra thousand island to dip, please 😋

Rueben Egg Rolls (24-30)
* 2.5 - 3lb cooked corned beef, cubed
* 16oz  Sauerkraut (we love @clekraut_ )
* 6oz swiss cheese, shredded 
* 1 tsp garlic powder
* 4 Tbsp minced Parsley 
* 2 package Egg Roll Wrappers (24-30 wrappers you need)
 ➖for assembly➖
* Cup of cold water
* Avocado Oil Spray (or nonstick spray of choice)
* Damp Paper Towel to cover egg rolls 

Pre heat oven to 400* 
spray baking sheet with nonstick spray
1. In a bowl, mix together the corned beef, sauerkraut, swiss cheese, parsley + garlic
2. Take one egg roll wrapper and lay down in a diamond ♦️ direction
3. Fill middle of egg roll wrapper with a few tablespoons of filling 
4. Tap your fingers into the cold water + run on all for edges of the egg roll wrapper 
5. ROLL! Start at the bottom corner, fold it over the filling, fold in each right + left corner towards the middle (press down to seal) and finally, rollll it up to the top
6. Seam side down onto the baking sheet and continue the process for all of the egg roll wrappers 
7. Keep rolled egg rolls covered with a large damp paper towel so they do not dry out!
8. When finished rolling, spray tops with non stick spray and BAKE at 400* for 8-10 minutes, flip and cook another 8-10 until they are kissed golden brown 
9. Serve with Thousand Island dressing for dunking 

If you’d like to make this ahead to freeze, simply follow directions and let the egg rolls cool completely. Lay in a single layer in a gallon freezer ziploc bag and freeze until ready to enjoy. When ready, place on a baking sheet with nonstick spray and warm through on 350* for 20-25 minutes

Broccoli Cheddar Soup
-loaded with veggies-

When it comes to veggies in soup? 
Gimme Gimme MORE!
My Broccoli Cheddar Soup is packed full of veggies and blended into a creamy soup that is out of this world! 
@micelidairy shredded sharp cheddar cheese🧀 makes this soup so flavorful, or shall I say, slurp-worthy 😋

🥣Broccoli Cheddar Soup🥣 
1 large onion, diced
2 cup shredded carrot 
1 Tbsp olive oil
3 cup cauliflower florets, chopped
4 cup broccoli florets, chopped
6 cloves garlic, smashed
64 ounces organic vegetable stock
1 tsp garlic + onion powder
2 bay leaf
8 ounces Micelis Sharp Shredded Cheddar
1/2-3/4 cup heavy cream
Salt + Pepper to taste 

Let’s cook!
In a dutch oven, sauté the onion + carrot with olive oil and a pinch of salt + pepper 
Once onions are translucent, add cauliflower, broccoli + garlic cloves
Pour in the vegetable stock, garlic powder, onion powder and bay leaf (you want enough stock to cover the veggies) 
Place a lid on and simmer for 30 minutes 
Remove lid + take out the bay leaf from the dutch oven 
Use an immersion blender and blend vegetables until smooth 
Add heavy cream + cheddar cheese, stir to combine - Season to taste 

Chefs Kiss 💋

ps.  roast some broccoli florets on a sheet pan drizzled with olive oil, lil’ salt + pepper at 375° for 25-30 min + garnish the soup with that + extra cheddar cheese 🧀

Broccoli Cheddar Soup loaded with veggies 🥕 🥦🧅

This soup is a delicious cross between zuppa tuscana + a vegetable soup and I am in love with the results! 
Feel free to cut this recipe in half, I always make enough for two nights or to have leftovers for lunch for a day or two 🖤
I started mine in a dutch oven and transfered to a crock pot to simmer all day long 

Creamy Tomato Sausage + Kale Soup 

2lb italian chicken sausage 
1 large onion
3 cup diced celery
4 cup diced carrot
LOTS of chopped garlic 🧄 

6oz organic tomato paste
28oz organic crushed tomatoes
64oz organic chicken stock
2-3 cup water
1 can northern beans, drained
1 tsp garlic powder, onion powder + oregano 
2 bay leaf 

Bunch of organic kale, chopped
1 cup + heavy cream 
season to taste with salt + pepper 

1. In a dutch oven over medium high heat, add the chicken sausage + a drizzle of olive oil. let sausage crumble + brown 
2. turn heat down to medium…remove sausage from pan + add in the carrot, celery, onion and garlic with a bit more olive oil, salt and pepper.  allow this to cook down for 5-8 minutes 
3. add tomato paste + stir to coat softened veggies. pour in the crushed tomatoes, chicken stock, spices + beans 
4. allow this to simmer for 45 -60 minutes 
5. Pour in heavy cream and chopped kale when you have 30 minutes left of simmering (add as much cream as you prefer, I did about 3/4 cup) 
Season to taste and ENJOY! 

* if you are vegetarian, this would be delicious with mushrooms to replace the chicken sausage.  Simply season mushrooms with italian seasoning + use vegetable stock 
*you can transfer soup to the slow cooker right after you add the crushed tomato and beans. simply let it sit on low all day and add the cream + kale 30 min prior to serving

Air Fryer Salmon Nuggets + Roasted Broccoli 

Healthy, nutritious + damn delicious - this dinner will literally make you do a happy dance at the table…
Mmm Mmm GOOD!! 
Air Fryer Salmon Nuggets get a quick marinade + then caramelized in the air fryer to perfection
Roasted Broccoli? Please tell me you’ve had it - it’s literally our entire families FAV way to eat broccoli 🥦 the crispy edges are irresistible! Brody will eat an entire batch 😋

Serve these in a bowl with white rice + yum yum sauce OR utilize the salmon in a salad or tacos 

(I used 3lbs of salmon - we love fish 🐟 so double or triple the recipe below if needed) 

🐟Air Fryer SALMON Nuggets🐟
1 lb Salmon, Wild Caught - cut into 1.5-2 inch cubes 
1 Tbsp sesame cooking oil (or olive oil)
1 Tbsp Hoisin Sauce
1 Tbsp Coconut Aminos 
1/2 tsp garlic powder
shimmy shake of black pepper 

🥦Roasted Broccoli 🥦 
Broccoli florets, cut into bite size pieces
Olive Oil, Salt + Pepper

🐟 Toss the salmon nuggets in the sesame cooking oil, hoisin, coconut amino, garlic powder + pepper 
🐟 Set air fryer @ 400° for 7-9 min + SPRAY the air fryer tray with non stick spray 
🐟 Place a single layer (spaced out) of salmon nuggets into the air fryer + cook for 7-9 minutes depending on size of salmon nugs ( I did 9 ) 

🥦Place broccoli onto a baking sheet, in a single layer; toss liberally with olive oil (don’t be shy with it!) salt + pepper - bake @ 400° for 30-40 minutes, tossing halfway through (let it get nice + crispy golden on parts) 

That’s it! ENJOY!

Air Fryer Salmon Nuggets are officially a favorite of the Thome fam 🖤 And don’t even get me started on roasted broccoli, it’s our # 1 vegetable side - always.

The Ultimate Egg Salad Sandwich 
w/Green Goddess Dressing + Micelis Provolone Cheese 

This sandwich, every single component of it will leave you weak in the knees. 
The options of what to use Miceli’s cheese for is limitless, breakfast lunch or dinner - there’s always a place for their cheese 😋

If you are an egg salad lover like me, hang onto your britches b/c this sandwich is SO flavorful with my green goddess yogurt dressing, each bite will make you say Mmm Mmm Mmm! 

SAVE this recipe for spring get together, would be delish in a croissant too! 

10 hard boiled eggs, peeled + chopped
3 Tbsp mayo
1 tsp dijon mustard 
Good pinch of salt + pepper 

Green Goddess Dressing 
2 cup parsley
1 oz basil 
.75 oz chives 
2 cup greek yogurt
Zest + Juice of 1 lemon
2 cloves garlic 
Salt + Pepper
Olive Oil

To make the egg salad, simply add the mayo, mustard, salt + pepper to the chopped eggs and stir to combine.  Store in fridge until you assemble the sammy’s

For the dressing, add the herbs to a food processor with a few tablespoons of olive oil. Blend to break them up a bit. 
Add greek yogurt, lemon zest + juice, garlic, good pinch of salt and pepper and another swirl of olive oil. Blend for 3-5 minutes until dressing is light and fluffy (store in fridge to enjoy on sandwiches/salads/as a dip all week)

To assemble the sandwich, toast 2 slices of your favorite bread
Smear green goddess dressing on both pieces of bread 
Add a slice of Micelis provolone to each 
Pile on slice with egg salad + a hefty handful of broccoli kale microgreens
Slice + enjoy!

The Ultimate Egg Salad Sandwich

Every family has a favorite chocolate chip cookie recipe, this is ours ❤️

Chewy, gooey + chocolate galore - this chocolate chip cookie recipe is perfection 

🍪Chocolate Chip Cookies🍪

2 sticks unsalted butter, @ room temp
1 cup sugar 
1/2 cup packed light brown sugar 
2 eggs @ room temp 
2 tsp vanilla 
3 cup flour 
1 tsp baking soda 
1/4 tsp salt 
10 oz bag of chocolate chunks 
flaked sea salt 

🍪In a stand mixer, whip together the butter + sugars until it’s super light + fluffy (6 minutes) scrape sides every few minutes 
🍪Add the eggs + vanilla and mix for another 4 minutes 
🍪Pour in the flour, baking soda + 1/4 tsp salt 
🍪Pulse the mixer so the cookie dough just comes together (no visible flour) 
🍪Stir in the chocolate chunks, saving a handful to top the cookies with
🍪KEY: use a cookie to to scoop the dough onto a parchment lined baking sheet 
🍪Add a few more chocolate chunks to the top + a sprinkle of flaked sea salt 
🍪BAKE at 350° for 9 min. Take the baking sheet out of the oven + smack the pan on the counter a few times to deflate the cookies slightly.  Back into the oven for 3 minutes - do not over bake 
🍪Remove from oven + let set on the baking sheet for a few minutes before moving to cooling rack

➖Dilly Dilly Potatoes➖
24 oz bag @melissasproduce baby dutch potatoes (or yukon gold cut into bite size) 
Enough to fill a baking sheet 
Generous drizzle of olive oil - few tablespoons 
1 tsp kosher salt
1/4 tsp pepper 
2 tsp garlic powder 
2 tsp dry dill weed 
2 tsp onion powder 

1. Place potatoes on baking sheet 
2. Drizzle generously with olive oil 
3. Shake on seasonings and toss toss toss
4. 375* for one hour, tossing 1/2 way through
*sometimes I do another 15 if I’m feeling frisky 
Enjoy!

Chicken Sausage + Spinach Mac n’ Cheese 
(this is to feed 6-8 feel free to halve recipe)

4 boxes Annie’s Shells & White Cheddar 
1 onion, diced 
2lb Sweet Italian Chicken Sausage 
16oz organic baby spinach 
1 cup milk 
1/2-1 cup pasta water
1/2 stick butter 
8oz bag of shredded provolone/mozzarella 

This entire meal is made in the time it takes to bring your water to a boil + cook your pasta! So quick, and absolutely delicious.  Doctoring up a basic mac n’ cheese makes dinner so easy + you can make dozens of variations. 

Let’s cook! 

1. Boil water for pasta shells, cook em’ for 7 minutes and reserve 1 cup of pasta water before draining 
2. While that’s happening, sauté the diced onion in a little olive oil until tender 
3. Add the chicken sausage, break it apart as it browns to achieve smaller bites (let it cook all the way through) 
4. Once the sausage is cooked through add the spinach, pop the lid onto your dutch oven and let simmer for a minute to wilt the spinach 
5. Remove sausage/spinach mix from the pot 
6. To the same dutch oven, pour in 1 cup of milk, butter, 1/2 cup pasta water and the 4 envelopes of cheese packets. Whisk on medium-low to bring to a gentle bubble
7. Pour in the pasta, stir to coat in sauce + then add in half of the bag of shredded cheese.  Toss to coat
8. Lastly, stir in the sausage/spinach mixture and top with the last of the shredded cheese + a little dried oregano 

at this point you can either let it cool completely and then store in the fridge to bake off that evening (lid on, 350° until warmed through) 
OR bake right away with the lid off at 350° until cheese is golden and bubbly - 10-15 min max 

ENJOY!!

3/4 tsp onion powder

Grab either a dutch oven OR your slow cooker to make the broth …

-What you’ll need for the dutch oven or slow cooker - 
2 organic bone in chicken breasts
4-6 carrots, cut into half
4-6 stalks of celery, cut in half
1 large onion, quartered 
TONS of garlic cloves (20 ish cloves) 
3 bay leafs 
Handful of parsley 
a few sprigs of herbs you like! I do thyme, sage & rosemary

🩵Stir in shredded chicken, lemon juice - salt and pepper to taste

@garlic.expressions dressing
parmesan cheese 
cooked spaghetti noodles
meatballs & @carbonefinefood marinara

1 1/2 tsp vanilla 
1/8 tsp almond extract 
1/2 cup light brown sugar 
1/2 cup sugar 
2 1/2 cup unbleached all purpose flour

1 1/2 tsp vanilla

🩵In a standard mixer, mix together the butter & cream cheese until smooth

You know when you find a recipe that ALL of your family members eat happily + you feel the need to shout it from the rooftops?! Yep, it’s this one 🩵

1 packet @sietefoods mild taco seasoning 
1/4 cup water
2 bell peppers, finely chopped
1 onion, finely chopped 
2 cups shredded taco blend cheese 
12+ 8 inch soft flour tortillas

In a dutch oven, add the chopped peppers & onions. Drizzle with a little olive oil, Salt + Pepper and let cool until the veggies are really tender (5 min) on medium heat

🌮Roll all tacos until tray is full (use two trays if needed)
🌮Brush taco roll ups with olive oil OR spray with olive oil spray

🌮FLIP and cook for another 7-8 until golden

 7 cups Peanut Butter Chex Cereal 
1 cup creamy Peanut Butter 
12 ounce bag @hersheys dark chocolate chips 
2 - 2.5 cup powdered sugar

salt & pepper

Pickles

Let’s GoOo!!

Nutritious Chicken Tortilla Soup 
2 @smartchicken_official bone in chicken breasts 
6 celery ribs, halved
6 carrots, halved 
1 large onion, quartered
28 ounces fire roasted tomatoes 
Tons of garlic cloves (15+) 
2 bay leaf
salt + pepper
8-10 cups water 
4 ounces canned diced chiles 
2 cans of black beans OR pinto beans
3/4 - 1 packet @sietefoods mild taco seasoning

🩵Place ALL of veggies from the broth into a blender along with a cup of broth & chiles and blend until fully pureed 
🩵Add all left over broth & pureed veggies back into the dutch oven OR a slow cooker & stir to combine 
🩵Pour in the taco seasoning 
🩵Add in the beans & shredded chicken

You are going to love it!! 
If you love tuna, this is like a tuna melt but with all the yummy toppings - pickled red onions, pickles - YUM!
Bonus? You don’t have to stand over a pan - let the oven do the work 
Assemble, bake + enjoy! 

Tuna Quesadilla 

2 (2.6 ounce) tuna packets, crumble the tuna 
1 (10 inch) flour tortilla 
Shredded Cheddar Cheese Blend 
Mayo 
Toppings: Pickled Red Onions, Dill Pickles, Banana Peppers, Jalapeños - whatever you like! 
Pinch of salt + Pepper 

Choose your own adventure here, loves
The more funky toppings the better!

Grab a sheet pan and preheat the oven to 425°
🩵drizzle a little olive oil onto the pan + plop the tortilla on top and rub it to coat the bottom side in oil
🩵Now, smear a tablespoon of mayo onto one half of the bare tortilla 
🩵Add the crumbled tuna evenly to the top of the mayo
and sprinkle with salt + pepper
🩵Top with pickles, red onions (banana peppers, roasted red pepper, jalapeño - lots of options here) 
🩵sprinkle over the shredded cheese to cover and then fold the empty half of the tortilla over top + press down to seal 
🩵Pop into the oven for 6-7 minutes on each side (flipping once) until golden brown
* I put my baking sheet on the bottom oven rack - just keep an eye on it*

My Olive Oil Banana Bread recipe is an oldie but goodie from the blog that we make on a weekly basis.  I love using a non inflammatory oil in replacement of vegetable oil when I can with baking. And this recipe has minimal added sugar which is awesome too! 

Get ready for your kiddos to inhale these 😋
This recipe yields 12-15 muffins 

You can swap olive oil 🫒 for avocado oil 🥑
Mix chocolate chips into the batter prior to scooping too! 

🍌Olive Oil Banana Muffins🍌

2 ripe bananas
1/2 cup packed brown sugar
3/4 cup buttermilk 
1/2 cup olive oil
1.5 tsp vanilla
2 eggs 
2 cup flour 
1 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp baking soda
1 tsp cinnamon
good pinch of salt 

🍌Mix together the bananas & sugar until smooth (very few clumps of banana left) 
🍌Add buttermilk, olive oil + vanilla,eggs and mix till everything is well incorporated 
🍌Pour in the flour, baking powder + soda, cinnamon + salt and mix until batter is smooth n’ shiny 
🍌Scoop batter into lined muffin pan (3/4 full) 
🍌Bake at 350° for 17-20 minutes (test with toothpick)

Loaded Veggie Taco Meat 

No strict recipe here, my friends! Simply a concept to packing our Taco night with extra veggies so the kiddos get all the good stuff in without the hassle 🩵

For every 1.5 pounds of meat I do 1 bell pepper, and one small onion
if it’s 2.5 - 3 pounds of ground beef I’ll do 2 large peppers and one large onion 
 
🧅 🫑 Finely diced, the smaller the better 
🥩 We love using organic ground beef 
🌮 Season your meat with your favorite taco seasoning ( we love @sietefoods ) 
🫙For every 1.5 pounds of meat I add roughly 1/4 cup @ortegataco mild taco sauce + 1/4 cup water 

🩵Start by sautéing the onion + peppers in a little olive oil with salt + pepper over medium heat until really tender
🩵Add the ground beef, season with salt and + pepper and turn up the heat to brown / cook meat (at this point make sure to break down your meat to a fine crumble) 
🩵Once meat is nearly cooked through, add the taco seasoning, mild Ortega sauce + water - stirring combine 
🩵Turn the heat to low and let simmer until cooked through 

Serve taco meat as you wish! Tacos, Nachos, Salads, Taquitos, Burittos etc

A handful of ingredients is all you need to make the most scrumptious & nutritious homemade protein bars for your family! These taste just like the famous peanut butter cups we all love, except are packed with incredible ingredients! 
Make a batch, and keep ‘em’ in your fridge for your crew to enjoy all week long 😋

🩵Peanut Butter Protein Bars🩵
2 cup creamy peanut butter 
1 1/2 cup unflavored Protein Powder*
1/2 cup ground flaxseed*
1/4 cup honey 
1 1/2 tsp vanilla 
pinch of salt 

2 1/2 cup dark chocolate chips, melted 
Flaked sea salt
Sprinkles 

Line a 9x9 baking pan with parchment paper
🩵In a large bowl, add the peanut butter, protein powder, flaxseed, honey, vanilla + salt
🩵Stir well, until everything is completely combined and you have a thick peanut butter batter
🩵Spread and press the peanut butter batter into the baking pan into an even layer
🩵Pour melted chocolate over the top + spread evenly 
🩵Sprinkle with flaked sea salt + sprinkles 
🩵
Pop into the fridge for one hour to set
Store in the fridge, covered and slice as needed 
*We love @vitalproteins collagen peptides for protein powder but use whatever you like.  Vanilla protein powder tastes amazing too - simply omit the vanilla extra in the recipe is using that!
*i love them with the layers reversed, let the chocolate harden in the bottom of the pan + do PB on top
*don’t panic if you don’t have ground flaxseed - simply increase the protein powder to 2 cups

These overnight oats 🏆
Oh em gee, my friends! I can’t stop talking about these!! 
Making a delicious & nutritious breakfast is so easy with my make-ahead overnight oats.  This little mason jars of oats are SO creamy, just sweet enough and topped with peanut butter 😋 YUM! 

Let’s make em’

🩵Overnight Peanut Butter & Blueberry Oats🩵
3 cup @onedegreeorganics oats
1/2 cup chia seeds
4 cup @oatly milk 
1/2 cup maple syrup
pinch of salt (we love @redmondrealsalt)
🫐 @wymansfruit frozen wild blueberries 
🥜Creamy peanut butter

In a large bowl mix together the oats, chia seeds, milk, maple syrup & salt 

- Grab 4 sixteen ounce wide mouth mason jars - 
🩵Place 1/4 cup frozen blueberries in the bottom of the jar 
🩵Fill the jar 3/4 full with the oat mixture (make sure liquids are covering oats) 
🩵Top with a 1.5 Tbsp  creamy peanut butter
🩵Seal the mason jar and store in the fridge overnight + enjoy in the morning cold OR warm em’ up in the microwave

*you can use any frozen berries you like! Strawberries, raspberries, blackberries etc

Who remembers Market Day?! Oh the 90’s nostalgia …
Their chocolate pudding cake/bread loaf had a hold on me like you would not believe 😋 Its exactly what inspired me years ago to create a healthier version that packs some secret veggie for the kids! This recipe turns out so tender and chocolatey and is kiddo approved🩵

PS. I like to store this in the fridge, just like Market Days Pudding Cake Loaf - it’s SO good cold!! 

🩵One Bowl Double Chocolate Zucchini Bread🩵

1/2 cup brown sugar, packed
1/4 cup honey
1/2 cup avocado oil
2 eggs 
2 tsp vanilla 
1 1/2 cup finely grated zucchini (do NOT squeeze excess water out) 
1 cup flour
1/2 cup cocoa powder
1 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp salt 
1 cup semi sweet or dark chocolate chips 

Grab a bowl friends, let’s bake!

Line a bread pan with parchment paper for easy removal 
Pre heat the oven to 350°

🩵Whisk together the brown sugar, honey, avocado oil, eggs and vanilla
🩵Stir in the grated zucchini 
🩵Add the flour, cocoa powder, baking soda + salt 
🩵Stir until batter is smooth + everything is fully incorporated 
🩵Add 3/4 cup chocolate chips and stir into the batter
🩵Pour batter into the bread loaf pan, spread into an even layer
🩵Sprinkle more chocolate chips on top bc YOLO 

Bake at 350° for 50-55 minutes, or until cooked through.  Insert a tooth pick in the center, and when pulled out there should be few crumbs attached ✅

This is my Go-To method for cleaning my wood cutting boards…

I really don’t like taking soap to my boards, and this method not only disinfects with the power of salt & lemon - I love that I don’t have to apply harsh products to my boards we use constantly throughout the day!

NOTE: I do NOT prep raw meat of any sorts on my wood cutting boards! 

🩵 Coarse Kosher Salt @mortonsalt 
🍋 1/2 Lemon

🍋Simply coat the cutting board in kosher salt 
🍋Squeeze the lemon juice all over to moisten the salt 
🍋Give the board a good scrub using the halved lemon and then allow the board to sit for 10 minutes 
🍋Use a bench scrapper for stubborn build up and then rinse with hot water 
🍋Let the board air dry completely 
🍋Replenish your dry boards by wiping a bit of olive oil onto the surface with a paper towel
